          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:018dc3ebfc22ea606f02a3ac18bb6fdf5e37de797b35a952d43aebefae1a0ff8",
          "at": "2026-06-30T03:47:11Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "The Codex provider path allows invoking the specialist \"directly via the codex CLI\" without requiring `--sandbox read-only`. In this repo the tracked `.codex/config.toml` defaults to `sandbox_mode = \"workspace-write\"`, and `.claude/rules/10-guardrails.md` warns that Codex workspace-write subprocesses can write files and run git operations outside Claude hook coverage. Since rollback-diagnoser is explicitly diagnose-only, this path should either require a repo-owned read-only wrapper or spell out `codex exec --sandbox read-only` and forbid `--full-auto`.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": ".claude/commands/track/diagnose.md",
              "line": 50,
              "category": "hook coverage gap"
            },
            {
              "message": "This command classifies `bin/sotp signal calc-*` as read-only inspection, but the existing signal command surfaces are compute-and-persist operations: `calc-spec-adr` persists into `spec.json`, and `calc-catalog-spec` / `calc-impl-catalog` generate signal JSON files. Allowing a diagnose-only command to run them can mutate SoT artifacts despite the command's \"does not edit any SoT artifact\" boundary. Limit this path to true read-only commands such as check/results, or make signal refresh an orchestrator-owned step outside rollback-diagnoser.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": ".claude/commands/track/diagnose.md",
              "line": 81,
              "category": "command wiring breakage"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:018dc3ebfc22ea606f02a3ac18bb6fdf5e37de797b35a952d43aebefae1a0ff8",
          "at": "2026-06-30T03:51:47Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "final",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "The Codex wrapper still classifies `signal calc-*` as a permitted read-only inspection command, but the capability SSoT now says rollback-diagnoser must not run mutating refresh commands such as `signal calc-*` and that signal refresh is orchestrator-owned. When `capabilities.rollback-diagnoser.provider` is switched to `codex`, these agent-level instructions are what the specialist receives, so the Codex path can mutate persisted signal artifacts during a diagnose-only flow while the Claude command/subagent path forbids it. This breaks the responsibility boundary and cross-host parity for the new capability; update the Codex agent boundary to match the SSoT/read-only command policy.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": ".codex/agents/rollback-diagnoser.toml",
              "line": 27,
              "category": "responsibility-boundary cross"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:90d2decd75c16c8163e63403f8345a99a65af086bd3b5ca090a478af14ea795f",
